      "date": "2026-04-20",
      "time": "20:54:38"
    },
    "16": {
      "answer": "The construct of value-added architecture describes how value-creating activities are structured and distributed across the supply chain. It shows which actors (suppliers, manufacturers, distributors) perform which activities and how they are connected. The goal is to optimize the overall value creation process, not just individual firm performance.",
